title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER SUPER X2 SPORTING CLAYS 12 ga. 3 in. FULL INVECTOR LNIB
postcontent:
Winchester's own advertising makes clear the advantages of the Super X 2 Active Valve system, a self-regulating system that allows shooters to manage anything from 12 gauge Bismuth 3 inch Magnums to Super Lite Target loads by the hundred in a single day without fatigue. The Super X 2 is furthermore capable of firing five shells in a half second. That puts it ahead of the fabled Benelli Black Eagle, both in speed and in felt recoil. In our traditionalist minds, Belgium wins over Italy by a long, long shot. This shotgun is manufactured, of course, in Belgium for Winchester. The 30 inch barrel is a proven performer for sight radius advantage and tight shooting; the Back-bored barrel with Invector Plus Choke tubes makes it an instant champion. Weighing in at 8 ½ pounds, this Super X 2 has a superior balance and feel. Stock and forend on this Clays edition is genuine European Walnut with cut checkering. Length of pull is standard 14 3/8 inches with pad; drop at comb is a sure handling 1.5 inches that descends to 2 3/8 at the heel; shims are included to adjust the drop and cant. This Super X 2 Clays comes with a total of 5 Invector Plus Choke Tubes: Skeet, IC, Mod, Improved Mod, and Full. In many respects, This Super X 2 is preferable to its Super X 3 replacement. The SX-2 variant is a few ounces heavier than its Super X 3 descendant. The Super X 3 sacrifices its steel magazine tube, and shooters prefer steel tubes any day. The Super X 3 is not even offered in 30 inch barrel with Walnut Stock in any configuration. Replacement price on this fine shotgun in our area is $900 or more if a person can even find one. We're offering this gun, however, for only $ 675.00 USD
